review_blob:
dark carmel color.relatively small white head.  spicey, mutty aroma.  great sourness/tartness.  expected more but nicely balanced with a little malt note.
pleasantly surprised.  thanks biggcb

very carbonated.  dark tan color with big white head with lots of yeast "chunks" in it.  aroma is mainly yeast with some spiciness and some other aroma I cant tell.   flavor is also very yeasty,  mostly dry with some sourness. very little malt flavor.  not too bad....for a very different style than Im used to.

amber with big white head.  mostly citrus aroma with some floral.  flavor is mostly malt with a decent hoppiness.  little yeasty.  surprising taht the alcohol is so high.  expected more hoppiness in a IIPA.

golden color with large white head. aroma is primarily citrus with some yeast and sourness.  mostly the same with the taste; citrus, sour, some spiciness and malt.  very drinkable.  good on hot day.  thanks biggcb
hops pretty much sums it up.  great citrus, floral aroma. Great hoppy flavor.  there is some malt flavor in there but dominated by hops. great beer

amber color with large dirty white head.  very hoppy aroma...mostly pine and citrus.  there is some maltiness in the aroma.  flavor again mostly hops.  pretty good brew.  always look forward to a Sly Fox.
UPDATED: JUN 20, 2007
chestnut color with small head.  great aroma of yeast, malt, dark fruits.  Very similar flavors.  very well balanced and alcohol is well disguised.  very good beer overall
pours dark amber/tan with a fairly small light tan head.  very malty aroma.  malty, bready flavor predominantly with some dark fruit underneath.  very complex and well-balanced.  a must try.
extremely dark with brown head.  aroma is coffee, chocolate/cocoa. very intense flavor dominated by coffee. Also chocolate and roasted malt.  a very interesting beer.

very dark with a good sized tan head. wonderful aromas: coffee, chocolate, lots of roasted malts.  Amazing flavors.. espresso, dark chocolate.  really deep, complex flavors with amazing mouthfeel. really great beer...thanks biggcb

very dark brown with decent tan head.  dark fruits and alcohol dominate the aroma.  very complex flavors...dark fruits, malt, yeast, maybe some honey....very well balanced and not overly boozy considering th 11.3%
very very good   a must try for anyone.
very dark brown with good size tan head.  very sweet amoma, lots of malt, lots of molasses...maybe some dark fruits.  surprisingly not alcoholly with 9.2%.  very, very good
UPDATED: MAY 29, 2007
light brown w/ medium head. fuity, malty aroma.  mostly molasses and malt flavor. nice mouthfeel. very good overall

thanks to biggcb for this one (of many)  had some trouble getting this into a pitcher (huge gusher).  off-white head carmel-brown color.  realy nice aroma- dark fruits, heavy malt.  similar flavors as well..dark malts, maybe a little honey and molassas. alcohol is very disguised.  very, very good.

by looking at some of the reviews we may have had a "bad" bottle.   no head, no carbonation.  too sweet and fairly thin taste and mouthfeel.  flavor wasnt too bad just not much to it.
may have to try again
great bottle but pours with no head. fairly sweet aroma and flavor.  a little too bozzy and to sweet.  not the best belgian s.a.  by any means.
pours very hazy amber color.  very malty aroma with some fruitiness.  Noticable hops flavor with malt and fruit flavors as well. totally unfamilier with the beer but very enjoyable...thanks biggcb
good sized head.  very effervesent in the glass.  good fruit and yeast aroma.  malt and yeast dominate the flavor.  a nice dry mouthfeel.  very good and very refreshing.

tried again after quite a while. very enjoyable.  very big white head.  hazy golden/yellow color.  very yeasty aroma with a little spiciness. definatly dry mouthfeel.  very good overall.  great bottle

pours very dark brown wih a fairly small tan head.  mostly roasted malt aroma with a little bit of chocolate.  Flavor is mostly roasted malt.  somewhat thin mouthfeel. good flavor overall just expected a little more out of it.
small-medium brown head.  nice caramell, chocolate aromas. good mouthfeel. more chocolate, malt with a little hop.  very nice Imp stout

dark brown/black  with good tan head.  chocolate, molasses aroma. very smooth mouthfeel. malty flavor predominantly with some dark fruits.  one of my first stouts and still a favorite readily available stout.
amber color with some haze.  good balance of aromas: malt, citrus.  good balance in the flavor. definate malt but with balanced amount of citrus/pine hop.  very good IIPA  alcohol is well disguised.
pours a golden amber with good size head.  aroma is mostly citrus with some pine.  Flavor is also citrus. decent hoppiness but really expected more.  nothing great.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Hoppin to Heaven IPA

review_blob: extremely drinkable..great hoppiness. just the right amount of maltiness underneath the hops.   very solid IPA
light brown color with big head.  very good spice and yeast aroma.  excellent malt flavors.  very good mouthfeel and the 8% is well disguised.  very good
UPDATED: MAY 2, 2007

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: UPenn  very big apple aroma.  really closer to a cider to me.  tasted much like apple cider.  very thirst quenching. will make a good summer "beer"

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: UPenn tasting. good head very wheaty aroma.  very crisp,  a little sweet with some spiciness.  pretty good overall.  need to retaste in the summer
from UPenn tasting. great hop aroma with citrus, pine nominating.  very crisp mouthfeels.  good malt/hop balance.  very good effort for a local brewer.
golden/orange color. very large frothy head.  malty aroma with nice levels of spice and fruitiness.  very carbonated mouthfeel. yeasty& spicy flavor. well disguised 9%. very good overall
UPenn tasting..pale golden color. very sweet aroma- honey, citrus.  Too sweet I guess from the honey and unfortunatley that is the dominant flavor.  surprising @ 9%

UPenn tasting again...very dark red - purple.  Excellent black berry/currant aroma.  Flavor is dominated by black current.  Good tartness.  seemed a little thin and could use even more base under the fruit.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: UPDATED: MAR 20, 2007
Draft...@UPenn tasting.  Again time not available for really sipping this beer.  very malty aroma.  some yeast and spice also in the aroma.  Alcohol is not well disguised.

also tasted @ UPenn 07 beer tasting.  very dark brown  with a very small head.  The bourbon aroma dominates.  Extremely boozy flavor.  way too much Jim Beam flavor.  In fairness I did not have enough time to really sit and sip this but generally I dont care for this type of overly boozy conditioning
draft @ 07 UPenn tasting. Aroma is primarily yeasty and spicy.  Slightly sweet flavor.  good malt flavor with the right amount of fruit and spice.  very carbonated.  very crisp mouthfeel.
very nice surprice.  tks  to my brother Chris.  This pours almost black with a tan head.   Roasted malt aroma with dark chocolate and coffee.  Great mouthfeel. alcohol is well disguised.  very good.
pours deep red with a pretty good head.  Good aroma - nicely fruity.  After this the flavor lacks any real presence.  Somewhat of a "fake" flavor overall.  A bit of a miss for Sly Fox
Like the DFH pumkin this is fair at best. some pumpkin aroma and flavors.  way too much cloves in this.

this is a comlete miss for me.  Im not a huge fan of the style anyway but this just didnt do much for me.  No pumpkin aroma or flavor for me.  is spicy - nutmeg or similar.
bottom choice from DFH for me

dark brown pour.  some roasted malt aroma, not much hop.  fiarly sweet flaovrs.  Overall too boozy.  9.5% is significant but the alcohol aroma and flavors dominate this beer and overpower some of the flavors I think they could have achieved.  Not my favorite Avery by far

thanks to my brother Chris for this one. pours golden/dark tan and cloudy with large head.  very sour aroma.  nicely sour with a touch of fruit.  very crisp and clean to be very thirst quenching.  I need to try this in the summer.  I did not think Id like this style but very good
very dark with average tan head.  nice malty aroma.  mostly malt flavor, coffee, with a little hoppiness.  very drinkable, makes for a great everyday beer.
good brown color w/ tan head.  very slight malt aroma. thin malt flavor.  slightly "funky" flavor.  not a bad beer just not much to it.  one and done for me
beer_name: Big Boss Bad Penny Brown Ale

review_blob: amber color with not much head.  mostly malty aroma with a slight hop note.  flavor is mostly citus and malt.  clean and drinkable just not a lot to this beer.
rather thin overall.  some roasted malts with a little chocolate countered with some hops.  Nothing notable in this beer.  Love the style overall but this beer was just a weak attempt at it.

Amber colored with a good size head.  Good hoppy aroma.  some citrus & floral notes.  Slight malty flavor topped by decent amount of hoppiness.  somewhat thin.  Not too bad just a little bit "light" for and IPS
beer_name: Carolina Beer Co. Cottonwood Endo India Pale Ale
